description:
Rochester, New York was a hub for the Advent believers for a few years in the 1850's, and was witness to much hardship and dedication. The first Adventist owned press lived in the White's home, along with several other young people who would work tirelessly to spread the message of God via publication. 

To find out more about Rochester and the first Adventist Press read our extended article on our website.
https://lineagejourney.com/read/sacrifice-and-commitment-in-rochester
